# Python Quality Rules

- Keep imports stable for both direct run and package-style run (support fallback imports when needed).
- Use explicit, user-facing error messages for ADB/BlueStacks failures.
- Avoid hardcoded magic values when they should come from `CONFIG/config.json`.
- For threaded GUI actions, keep UI updates on the Tk main thread (`root.after` pattern).
- Add or update tests when changing launcher contracts, file paths, or config behavior.
